comment.shortText:
Client that interfaces with Senseye's REST API. Provides wrapper functions for
standard GET, DELETE, POST and PUT requests, as well as specific Senseye endpoints.

comment.text: Domain name or IP address of the API host. e.g. api.senseye.co[:80]
URL path prefix that'll be appended to `host`.
API key.

comment.returns: A `Promise` that will produce a {@link ComputeJobResponse}.

comment.text: Job ID produced after a successful call to {@link startPrediction | startPrediction()}.

comment.shortText: Submits a job to perform predictive analysis on a specified list of videos.
comment.text: https://app.swaggerhub.com/apis-docs/senseye-inc/senseye-api/0.0.1#/default/post_predict
comment.returns: A `Promise` that will produce a {@link ComputeJobInitResponse}.

comment.text: Value between 0.0 and 1.0; determines `prediction.state` in the final result.
Username or ID of the participant.

comment.shortText:
Class that models a session, facilitating the gathering and association of event
and video data generated during a participant's interaction with on-screen
stimuli, i.e. task or series of tasks.

Initializes the specified video and associates it with the session.
See {@link getVideos | getVideos()}.

comment.text: Instance of an uninitialized `Video`.

comment.returns: An array of videos associated with the session.

comment.shortText:
Creates a session model with the specified parameters. Note this should only be
done once per instance. Ensure initialization is successful before executing
certain functions within this class, otherwise errors may be thrown..
comment.returns: A `Promise` that will produce the created session's metadata.

comment.text: Client configured to communicate with Senseye's API.

Custom username or ID of the participant. Must be unique to the
                     participant within the context of the API key passed into the client.

ID of a {@link Survey} to associate to the session. Will ideally be
                     the demographic survey pertaining to the participant.

comment.shortText:
Class that models a survey, facilitating the collection of a participant's responses
to survey questions.

comment.text: Survey type, e.g. `demographic`, `validation`.

Map of keys to a tuple containing a corresponding question and response.
                     e.g. { 'eye_color': ['What color are you eyes?', 'Brown'] }
Any extra information or metadata.

Adds an entry for a question and its corresponding response. If `key` already
exists, the previous entry values will be overwritten.

comment.text: Key used to associate `question` and `response`.
Question or prompt value.
Response value to `question`.

comment.returns: A tuple containing question and response entries, respectively.

Component that executes a series of {@link Tasks} passed in as children elements (`props.children`).
